Package com.strandgenomics.imaging.icore

Interface Summary
Disposable Disposable objects must implement this
IAttachment Attachment (to a record) can be any file one wishes to associated with a record
IChannel Represents a channel of a record
IExperiment A list of records acquired under a given experimental condition Typically a multi-site/multi-series collection of records
ImageSource A source or provider of image within a record
IPixelData An pixel-data (raw pixel 2d image) within a record is uniquely identified by the 4 dimensions - (slices, frames, sites, channels) in addition to its x and y coordinates.
IPixelDataOverlay An overlay of two or more channels
IProject  
IRecord Record is a collection of images possibly specified in six dimensions (x,y,z,time,site,channel) and associated with a single acquisition instance
IRecordObserver  
ISourceReference Specification of a source file producing an experiment (muti-series records)
ITicket  
ITile A tile or rectangular block within a pixel data
IValidator  
IVisualOverlay Visual Object are a collection of visual objects (shapes/graphic-paths)
Storable Any class interested in accessing the data access layer would need to extends this marker interface
 

Class Summary
Channel Represents a channel of a record
Constants This class holds all constants for needed by iengine
Constants.Property Bunch of system properties to access global system variables Generally global variables are not a good idea, and therefore direct access to these system properties must be avoided
Dimension An pixel-data (raw bitmap image) within a record is uniquely identified by the 4 dimensions - (slices, frames, sites and channels).
History History of changes on a record
MetaData metadata represented as Name-Value pair
NavigationBin Represents a new FilterCondition on top of an existing list of FilterConditions
SearchCondition A column (field) with its lower and upper limits defines a search condition
SearchField represents a field that is searchable
Signature This class represents the Unique signature of a record
Site Represents a site of a record.
SourceFormat Represents a source format
Thumbnail Thumbnail powered by byte array
ThumbnailDimension Dimensions that identify a configuration of image(s) and used to generate thumbnail
UserComment Comments on a record by users
VisualContrast Contrast of a pixel data
VODimension Dimensions required for VisualOverlay it contains frame number, slice number and overlay name overlays will be shallow copied across the channels within THIS dimension
 

Enum Summary
AnnotationType used for annotation type to DB table mapping
ImageType  
Permission User has a permission in project
Rank A user has a rank in the institution
RecordMarker the status of the record: Active/Deleted/Archived etc
Status Status of a Job executed system the system
